#. +> trunk5
#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:16
msgid "The **Wall-Paper** tool allows setting an image from your collection as a background photo on your desktop. If you use a multi-screen computer, the image is assigned to the current monitor where digiKam is running."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:18
msgid "Select one image that you want to place on your desktop and go to :menuselection:`Tools --> Set as wallpaper`, or use the icon **Set as wallpaper** from the **Tools** tab on the right sidebar. A dialog will appear to customize the **Wallpaper Layout** of the background photo. The possible choices are:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:20
msgid "**Adjusted**: The image is resized to the desktop size without preserving the aspect ratio (Linux and Windows)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:21
msgid "**Adjusted with Aspect ratio**: The image is resized to the desktop size preserving the aspect ratio (Linux only)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:22
msgid "**Adjusted and cropped**: The image is resized to the desktop size and cropped to support the desktop aspect ratio (Linux only)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:23
msgid "**Mosaic**: The image is displayed multiple times as a mosaic to fill the desktop (Linux and Windows)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:24
msgid "**Centered**: The image is centered on the desktop without modification (Linux and Windows)."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../post_processing/wall_paper.rst:28
msgid "This dialog does not exist under macOS. The layout is always set as **Centered**."
msgstr ""

